OL,3,CMother and brother deny killing
OL,4,Cteenager in house fire
OL,6,FRichard Wright KC, prosecuting, said a
OL,7,Ffourth defendant Craig Watson, who was
OL,8,Falso charged in connection with the
OL,9,Fincident, had died in prison.
OL,11,FThe three defendants were granted bail
OL,12,Fahead of a four-week trial due to
OL,13,Fstart on October 5.
OL,15,FNorthumbria Police initially treated
OL,16,Fthe fire as arson, and at the time Ms
OL,17,FCasson's loved ones paid tribute,
OL,18,Fsaying: "Leah was an outgoing, bubbly
OL,19,Fyoung woman who we loved so much and
OL,20,Fwe can't believe she has gone.
